Date: 0/0/1941
Source: NZ Slang
Author: BAKER
Vol / Page: 50
Edition:
Quote: Among ... terms originated in the first Great War (are) ... <i>chatty</i> or <i>chati,</i> a louse (the versions <i>koota</i> and <i>kooti</i> from the Maori <i>kutu</i>, a louse, had been in use much earlier).
